<br>
Ok, I've been asked to come here.. So I am here.<br>
<br>
Maybe you don't know how to read xferlog's, just incase, I'm going to now show you:<br>
Sat Jan 25 17:55:40 2003 0 cs2416777-198.houston.rr.com 0<br>
/home/friends/isengard/public_html/cgi-bin/Database/message_data/message_data-99-997028564.db<br>
a _ d r isengard ftp 0 *<br>
<br>
First we have a date.  Second we have the IP of the person being logged into the FTP site.  Then we have the path to the file in question.  Then some more junk, then we have the action &quot;d for delete&quot;, r for real login, user isengard, via ftp.<br>
<br>
So that tells us 24.167.77.198 deleted the files.  That's houston, tx roadrunner.  By grepping bdm files we are able to extract usable information from them, mind you most everything is non-readable.  We look for all matches left for the IP, we find about 12 posts, 10 by megara, 2 by her daughter, we check this by looking at the first record in the posts.  Pasting this won't happen since they are binary for the most part and pretty hard to decipher.  We confirm this by checking out other information on our lead, and low and behold Megara does live in Houston, TX.  We then check session logs by session ID from our apache logs, and low and behold the session is Megara's.  So we now know for fact that it did begin from her computer.  Where more than likely the login and password are stored in here FTP client.<br>
<br>
We check out active sessions at that time and find the following:<br>
Brena|^|b^A^A3e331f6b4e64ffff|^|Brena|^|br//Ssw0jbTXI|^|66-1013995495|^|24.167.77.198|^|1043537771|^|Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 6.0; Windows 9<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
So it's safe to assume that Brena or Megara did it.  Her daughter was active on the boards 10 minutes prior to the event occuring, this is checked again by our access_log.<br>
<br>
(Space added in paths to make sure this doesn't truncate anything)<br>
