Lalala, (Notice the session IDs match prefectly as well).  Reads some posts.. Deletes some files on the FTP.  Megara was given the password, could possibly be stored on her computer, who knows.  I do know this is pretty much cutt and dry.  The delete came from Megara's computer, Megara's IP.  Brena was logged in, and boom, 5 minutes later the FTP is deleted by the same IP.<br>
<br>
There you have it.  Just have OOP or any other guild match the IPs and you know for sure it's from her computer, nothing more to talk about.. Who you accuse it up to you, you have the information, that's it.<br>
<br>
Now, why on earth would you want an <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="httpd.conf">onf</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> file?  It's an apache configuration file, it's pretty cutt and dry, spelling out virtualhosts, namevirtualhosts, it's written by the system admin only, and is not a log file.  Please enlighten me why you would need this?<br>
<br>
Furthermore, I don't like being called a stupid admin, or eluding to such a thing.  Before you start rambling off things you want and need, learn what they are; learn how to read the material you are presented.  If you don't understand, ask questions before you elude to me being an incompetent web admin, furthermore, I'm not a web admin, I'm a network administrator/systems administrator, and I oversee the operations of well in excess of 2,000 clients, colo servers, and others.  ShellBox Networks is my own little pet project the company permits me to run.<br>
<br>
Yes, there's always the possability with the admin falisfying the logs, if you don't trust me, I don't really care.  I have nothing to gain except a headache.  I DO NOT GET PAID FOR PROVIDING ISENGARD'S WEBSITE.  I WAS REIMBURSED ONCE FOR DOMAIN EXPENSES, NOTHING MORE.  There is no one paying any sort of monthly fee or the likes.  Megara does not OWN the website nor was she ever the person I had originally given access to.  Access was passed on to megara by another party.  I have nothing against Megara, infact I don't even really know her.  I remember her being a member of the guild when I was involved which a couple years ago but that's it.<br>
<br>
